installed-deps-atom: Rework internals in terms of new portage-utils

Newer portage utils can:
- Scan all dependency grades for all dependencies for all installed
  packages in a single pass
- Support internal implementation of "anti-slot" matching
- Supports output formatting that extracts installed slot for us
- Supports inbuilt repression of redundant parts of results

This means one can now do:

  emerge -va1 "$(
      qdepends -CqqdrpbQ                 \
               -F "%{CAT}/%{PN}:%{SLOT}" \
                  "^dev-lang/perl:0/5.30"
  )"

And assuming the output list doesn't exceed bash command-passing
limits, work as a good proxy for this entire tool

changelog: reimplement installed-deps-atom mechanic w/ new portage-utils

installed-match-atom: Reimplement in terms of newer qlist

qlist can do everything this code previously, did, and avoids
us needing to call portageq.
